{
  "doc_id": "35216",
  "text": "There has been a controversy as to the type of lymphoma cells, which is confined to the vascular lumina in this particular condition. Reduced expression of L 2 integrin (LFA-1, CD11a/CD18), a cell adhesion molecule related to invasivity, has been found once, [CITATION_1] but its relevance remains controversial. [CITATION_2] This is the third report to look into the cytogenetic abnormality of IVL, [CITATION_3] as it may be a clue to the unique phenomenon of lymphoma cell invasion. The chromosomes 16 and 21 bearing L 2 integrin genes were normal in our patient. The monosomy of chromosome 6 carrying the HLA gene shares the same abnormality as a previous reported case. The monosomy of chromosome 19 bearing the intercellular cell adhesion molecule-1 gene was found only in the present patient, although the relevance of this abnormality has yet to be studied.",
